We need to calculate $G^{\Vert}_{\mu\nu}=H_\mu^\lambda H_\nu^\rho G_{\lambda\rho}$. Let $l$ be 
a unit vector tangent to the entangling line. One has
\begin{eqnarray}
G_{\mu\nu}=\delta_{\mu\nu}-l_\mu l_\nu\, .
{\label}{ie-8}
\end{eqnarray}
Therefore,
\begin{eqnarray}
G^{\Vert}_{\mu\nu}=H_{\mu\nu}-l^{\Vert}_\mu l^{\Vert}_\nu\, ,
{\label}{ie-9}
\end{eqnarray}
where $l^{\Vert}_\mu=H_\mu^\lambda l_\lambda$.

Let us choose the basis $\hat{p}_i$ such that $\hat{p}_2$ is directed along the $x^0$ 
axis, while $\hat{p}_1$ is directed along the $x^1$. Then vector $l^{\Vert}$ is directed 
along $\hat{p}_1$, and one can easily see that  $l^{\Vert}=\sin\alpha~ \hat{p}_1$.
With these definitions,

